Title: Split housekeeping into git-cleanup phase and ticket-scan phase
Status: open
Created: 2026-04-27
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-27T00:00Z claude created

--- body ---
## Problem

Housekeeping does two expensive things in one session:
1. Git hygiene: stale branches, worktrees, STATE.md, commit
2. Ticket scan: sweep-skip expiry, pick-assessments

Combining them in a single long session (30–41 turns, $0.50+) means a budget
overflow in phase 2 undoes partially-committed phase 1 work visually (hk:rc=1 even
if the git cleanup was committed).

## Solution

Run housekeeping in two sequential sub-calls from beat.py:
1. `run_skill("/housekeeping-git", budget=0.35)` — git only, always runs
2. `run_skill("/housekeeping-tickets", budget=0.40)` — ticket scan, runs only if
   there are tickets to re-assess

Each can succeed independently. Beat.py marks hk:done if phase 1 succeeds, even
if phase 2 is skipped or fails.

## Acceptance criteria

- Git cleanup always completes within $0.35 budget
- Ticket scan is optional and skippable
- beat.py distinguishes hk-git:done from hk-tickets:done in the log

## Notes

Requires new skill files and beat.py changes. Larger effort than 0031/0032.
